# 🧪 2. Your fear: “What if bad code slips through?”

Let’s address that directly.

## ❌ Misconception

> “Cache might skip running tests, so bad code passes”

## ✅ Reality

Nx cache is **content-aware + hash-based**

It only reuses results if:

```plaintext id="hash1"
same code + same dependencies + same inputs
```

---

# 🔥 Example

## Case A — clean code already tested

You push:

```ts id="good1"
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}
```

✔ CI runs tests
✔ Result cached

Next time same code → reuse result

---

## Case B — bad code change

You push:

```ts id="bad1"
function add(a, b) {
  return a - b; // bug introduced
}
```

👉 Nx detects:

* file changed ❌
* hash changed ❌

✔ cache is NOT used
✔ tests RUN again
✔ bug is caught

---

# 🧠 3. Important rule

Nx cache NEVER skips execution when input changes.

It only skips when:

```plaintext id="rule1"
inputs identical → reuse result
inputs changed → re-run everything
```

---

# 🧸 4. Simple analogy

Think of Nx cache like this:

* You cooked rice 🍚
* You wrote down recipe result “OK”

Next time:

* If recipe is EXACTLY same → reuse note
* If anything changed → cook again

👉 It NEVER assumes new food is safe

---

